Abortion Compromise Laws in Christianity Religion

Society, especially the Christians in the United States, has been divided on the issue of abortion. There are advocates against the practice of abortion and there are also advocates for the practice of abortion. Prior to the 1973 Roe v. Wade decision, the decision to end a pregnancy was left in the hands of the states.

Pro-life vs Pro-choice January 3, 2017 Probably one of the most popular debates in our society with the topic of abortion is for the federal government to make other decisions for women on the issue of health.
